					<head>Derushim</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85085046" rend="visible">
						<summary>Short derushim on the events and ordinances contained in the Pentateuch (arranged in the order of weekly section), by Shemu'el ben Elisha' Portaleone.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85085046">
							<locus from="1r" to="244v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Derushim</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">דרושים</title>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en">Shemu᾿el ben Elisha῾ Portaleone</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he">פורטלאונה, שמואל בן אלישע</persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>The first series of the derushim ends on folio 203r.</p>
								<p>Folios 204-230 contain derushim on the weekly sections of Genesis and some other portions of the Pentateuch.</p>
								<p>Folio 231 contains an index headed: Sefer mizmorim. The column for the Psalms has not been filled in.</p>
								<p>Folios 232-241 embody further sipurim from a musaric Sefer ha-yashar. </p>
								<p>The rest of the manuscript contains some midrashic notes headed Kelale midrashim ve-ḥidushim ha-Torah.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex; Italian cursive script of the 17th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper codex.</support>
								<extent>244 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>285</height>
										<width>178</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>285</height>
										<width>155</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>244 folios (+ 3 modern and 1 older paper flyleaves at the beginning and 3 modern paper flyleaves at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of mostly 10-12 leaves each (irregular).</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>Several folios slightly mutilated.<p>Slightly stained.</p>
									<p>The ink has eaten through the pages.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="1 50" writtenLines="1 50">
									<p>Various page layouts. </p>
									<p>Visible vertical pencil ruling, frequently not respected by the scribe (e.g. folio 97r). Often no space is left for the margins.</p>
									<p>Several scribal erasures.</p>
									<p>Many pages left half or entirely blank (e.g. 227r-228r, 243r-244r).</p>
									<p>Watermark (recurrent) in the shape of a capricorn or a horse, undertermined.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Italian cursive script of the 17th century.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Folio 231 contains an index, headed Sefer mizmorim.</p>
						</additions>
